# Runbook

The session-routing playbook. Match intent to skill chain.

---

## Session starts

| Trigger | Chain |
|---|---|
| Cross-domain check ("where am I?") | `/briefing` |
| Mid-week focused build session | `/wiki-digest <topic>` -> proceed |
| Coming back to a stale project | `/briefing` -> `/wiki-brief <project>` |
| Capture an idea for a future cold-start session | `/idea-kickoff` |

[TODO: build phase 3 (workflow) refines these chains based on your harness + workflow preferences]

---

## Capture chain

When something worth ingesting arrives:

| Source | Chain |
|---|---|
| YouTube URL | `/ideaverse-os capture <url>` -> auto-routes to yt-light-research |
| Web page | Save via Obsidian Web Clipper -> `/ideaverse-os capture` (auto-detects drop) |
| Plain idea / "I learned X" | `/ideaverse-os capture "I learned ..."` -> direct synthesis |

---

## Reflection chain

| Trigger | Chain |
|---|---|
| End of work session | Stop hook fires `save-session.py` -> writes `70-daily/<date>-session-N.md` |
| Daily reflection (cron) | `reflect.py` -> reads past 24h logs -> promotes to `memory.md` |

---

## Compass-first rule

Any briefing or daily-note skill MUST lead its response with a one-line quote of `compass.md`'s "What I'm Optimizing For Right Now / This week" line. The compass is the priority filter.
